{
  "message": "test(corpus): canonicalize dogfood captured_at to epoch zero (ft-sz7lc)\n\nAll eight `<name>_dogfood_*.meta.json` fixtures stored literal wall-clock\ncapture timestamps. pattern_corpus.rs at :88-98 only asserts ISO-8601\n*shape*, so these exact strings aren't semantically fenced \u2014 but they\nare byte-frozen golden artifacts. Every dogfood recapture churns the\ngolden with incidental clock drift, and reviewers can't tell behavioural\nchange from wall-clock change at a glance.\n\nReplace all eight captured_at values with the canonical placeholder\n`\"1970-01-01T00:00:00Z\"`. Real acquisition date is already encoded in\nevery filename (`_dogfood_YYYY_MM_DD_*`) and, for finer provenance, in\nthe `notes` field, so no information is lost \u2014 just diff noise.\n\nREADME updated: adds a \"captured_at is a canonical placeholder\" note to\nthe Dogfood metadata section and bumps the example snippet. No\npattern_corpus.rs change needed; the existing shape assertion still\npasses epoch zero.\n\nAgent: RusticMeadow\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
